mbinations|combination]] as Torterra.\n* When walking to the right in [[Amity Square]], Torterra\'s sprite erroneously shows its left side.\n* Torterra is the [[List of Pokémon by weight|heaviest]] final form of a [[starter Pokémon]], weighing 683.4&nbsp;lbs. (310.0&nbsp;kg).\n\n===Origin===\n{{Bulbanews|On the Origin of Species: Turtwig, Grotle and Torterra}}\nTorterra has aspects of a {{wp|Chelydridae|snapping turtle}} and an {{wp|Ankylosauria|ankylosaur}}, armored dinosaurs. Its large features and spikes may also be inspired by extinct \'\'{{wp|Meiolania}}\'\' and \'\'{{wp|Proganochelys}}\'\' turtles. In concept, it may be based on the {{wp|World Turtle}}s in various mythologies that carry worlds upon their backs, or perhaps the {{wp|Black Tortoise}} of Asian legend.\n\n====Name origin====\nTorterra is a combination of \'\'tortoise\'\' and \'\'terra\'\' (Latin for \'\'ground\'\'). \'\'Terra\'\' may also refer to \'\'{{wp|terrapin}}s\'\'. It also bears similarity to \'\'{{wp|tuatara}}\'\' (a reptile similar to a lizard) and \'\'{{wp|totara}}\'\' (a type of tree), both found in {{pmin|New Zealand}}.\n\nDodaitose may be a combination of 土 \'\'do\'\' (earth or ground), 大 \'\'dai\'\' (large), and \'\'tortoise\'\'. It may also involve 土台 \'\'dodai\'\' ({{wp|Foundation (engineering)|foundation}}).\n\n==In other languages==\n{{Other languages|type=Grass|type2=Ground\n|ja= ドダイトス \'\'Dodaitose\'\'|jameaning=From {{tt|土 \'\'do\'\'|earth or ground}}, {{tt|大 \'\'dai\'\'|large}}, {{tt|土台 \'\'dodai\'\'|foundation}} and \'\'tortoise\'\'\n|fr=Torterra|frmeaning=Same as English name\n|es=Torterra|esmeaning=Same as English name\n|de=Chelterrar|demeaning=From {{tt|\'\'Chelonia\'\'|Greek for turtle}} and \'\'{{tt|terra|Latin for \'earth\'}}\'\'\n|it=Torterra|itmeaning=Same as English name\n|ko=토대부기 \'\'Todaibugi\'\'|komeaning=From {{tt|토 (土)\'\'to\'\'|Earth}}, {{tt|대 (大)\'\'dae\'\'|large}}, and {{tt|거북이 \'\'geobugi\'\'|turtle}}. Also involves {{tt|토대 \'\'todae\'\'|foundation}}.\n|zh_cmn=土台龜 / 土台龟 \'\'Tǔtáiguī\'\'|zh_cmnmeaning=Can be taken as "Earth terrace tortoise".\n<!--|zh_yue=土台龜 \'\'Tóutòihgwāi\'\'|zh_yuemeaning=Same as Mandarin name-->\n|hi=टोरटेरा \'\'Torterra\'\'|himeaning=Transliteration of English name\n}}\n<br clear="left">\n\n==Related articles==\n* [[Ash\'s Torterra]]\n* [[Paul\'s Torterra]]\n* [[Tru]]\n* [[Starter Pokémon]]\n\n==External links==\n\n{{-}}\n{{PokémonPrevNext/Head|type=Grass|type2=Ground}}\n{{PokémonPrevNext/Pokémon|type=Grass|prevnum=388|prev=Grotle|nextnum=390|next=Chimchar}}\n|}\n{{Project Pokédex notice}}\n\n[[de:Chelterrar]]\n[[es:Torterra]]\n[[fr:Torterra]]\n[[it:Torterra]]\n[[ja:ドダイトス]]\n[[zh:土台龟]]'}